The third approach which uses a fairly simple python script to change the users volume

Installing
1)install opencv using pip
2)if you dont have pip then look up a guide on how to install pip
3)download and run the python script

Using
1)once the program runs it will take camera inputs to adjust the volume based off of the users hands
2)once the required volume is achived press "spacebar" to set the volume and close the program

